genresAdvancedInfo.name: circus
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A genre of music that is inspired by the sights and sounds of the circus. It is characterized by its use of whimsical, playful melodies and instrumentation, including accordions, calliopes, and other carnival-style instruments. Circus music often features a fast tempo and upbeat rhythms that are meant to evoke the excitement and energy of the circus atmosphere. It is often used in films, commercials, and other media to add a sense of fun and whimsy to the proceedings.
